  <claims id="claims">
    <claim id="CLM-00001" num="00001">
      <claim-text>1. A method for routing inference requests in a neural network system, the method comprising:
        <claim-text>receiving an input token sequence at a gating network;</claim-text>
        <claim-text>computing, by the gating network, a routing score for each expert subnetwork of a plurality of expert subnetworks;</claim-text>
        <claim-text>selecting a subset of the expert subnetworks based on the routing scores, wherein the gating network is trained with an auxiliary load-balancing loss; and</claim-text>
        <claim-text>generating an output by combining results from the selected subset.</claim-text>
      </claim-text>
    </claim>
    <claim id="CLM-00002" num="00002">
      <claim-text>2. (canceled)</claim-text>
    </claim>
    <claim id="CLM-00003" num="00003">
      <claim-text>3. The method of <claim-ref idref="CLM-00001">claim 1</claim-ref>, wherein the routing scores are normalized with a softmax function.</claim-text>
    </claim>
